tiger-data-app.title: Started adding code to add read-only and read-write users via JavaScript
The "Data Sponsor" field is required, singular, and auto-populates the NetID of the person who launched the form

The "Project Directory" field is required, singular, and accepts a string of up to 64 Unicode alphanumeric, minus-dash, and/or underscore characters (or a suitable alternative method for ensuring that values are file path-safe on all systems)
If one clicks the "Cancel" button at any time, one is returned to the preliminary dashboard page (and no draft DOI is reserved)
The "Description" field is required, singular, and accepts a Unicode string value with no character restrictions or limits
If one clicks the "Submit" button, the form validates the entered values according to the above criteria
If the form values are successfully validated upon clicking "Submit", then a draft DOI is reserved from DataCite and recorded as the value for the "Project ID" field in the background
After the message is sent to the Product Owner, the user is taken to a page titled "New Project Request Received"
The "New Project Request Received" page contains a short message thanking the submitter and notifying them of the projected timeline for a response, followed by a "Return to Dashboard" button

Clicking the "Return to Dashboard" button returns the user to the preliminary dashboard page, where now the title of the newly created project, with an indicator for "Pending", is appended to the list of projects in the "My Sponsored Projects" section
Clicking a project title takes one to a "Project Details" page

If the project in question is still pending, then the "Project Details" page displays the following message immediately after the page title: "Your new project request is in the queue. Please allow 5 business days for our team to review your needs and set everything up. For assistance, please contact tigerdata@princeton.edu."
The "Project Details" page has 4 headings: "Roles", "Description", "Automatic Settings", and "Provenance"
Under the "Roles" heading, the page displays the full names of all persons currently assigned to each role: "Data Sponsor", "Data Manager", and "Data User(s)"
If no one is assigned as a Data User, then the page displays "(none)" next to "Data User(s)"
If multiple Data Users are assigned, then the page displays the full names of all Data Users in a comma-separated list, sorted alphabetically by family name
If any Data Users are marked as "Read Only", then the page displays "(read only)" after each applicable name
If multiple Affiliated Departments were selected, then all departments display in a comma-separated list, sorted alphabetically

Under the "Automatic Settings" heading, the page displays the current values for the following project metadata fields: "Project ID", "Storage Capacity", "Storage Performance Expectations", and "Project Purpose"
Under the "Provenance" heading, the page displays the current values for "Submission" and "Status"
At the bottom of the page, there are two buttons: "Return to Dashboard" and "Withdraw Project Request"
Preliminary review of sponsored projects
After a validated form is submitted and the "Project ID" value is recorded, an email is sent to the Product Owner containing a submission timestamp and the project metadata record in XML or JSON

tiger-data-app.title: Preliminary project creation form

On the "Project Details" page, if the project has been approved and if the user is filling the role of Data Sponsor or Data Manager, then the "Roles" and "Description" headings display an "Edit" button next to each
Clicking either "Edit" button takes the user to the "Project Revision Request" form

The "Project Revision Request" is formatted almost identically to the "New Project Request" form, except that the fields are all populated with the current values for each, and that if the user is a Data Manager, then the "Data Sponsor" and "Data Manager" fields are uneditable (because only Data Sponsors can make such changes)
If no changes have been made to the form, or if any field contains an invalid entry, then the "Submit" button at the bottom of the form is deactivated

If changes have been made, then clicking the "Submit" button takes the user to the "Project Revision Request Received" page, which contains the same message and button as the "New Project Request Received" page
